00:11:59.310 --> 00:12:07.620 align:middle line:10%
is, roughly speaking, 240
some odd generations after--

00:12:07.620 --> 00:12:08.730 align:middle line:10%
After what?

00:12:08.730 --> 00:12:12.510 align:middle line:84%
There's an instance in the
past, an incident that happened,

00:12:12.510 --> 00:12:15.210 align:middle line:90%
which he thinks of as the fall.

00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:17.460 align:middle line:84%
And what this was,
apparently, was the collapse

00:12:17.460 --> 00:12:19.680 align:middle line:90%
of Western civilization.

00:12:19.680 --> 00:12:21.420 align:middle line:90%
He lives in a time, roughly--

00:12:21.420 --> 00:12:26.250 align:middle line:84%
If you convert 247 generations
into 20 years per generation,

00:12:26.250 --> 00:12:28.830 align:middle line:84%
it comes out to
roughly 5,000 years.

00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:31.650 align:middle line:84%
This man, if my
calculations are correct,

00:12:31.650 --> 00:12:34.960 align:middle line:84%
lives roughly 5,000
years from now.

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:39.480 align:middle line:84%
>> So you're looking
out of this man's eyes.

00:12:39.480 --> 00:12:42.530 align:middle line:84%
Where is he, and
what do you see?

00:12:42.530 --> 00:12:45.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, he's living on the
Western coast of North America.

00:12:45.080 --> 00:12:46.640 align:middle line:90%
He knows this.

00:12:46.640 --> 00:12:49.760 align:middle line:84%
He's living in a part of
the world which today we

00:12:49.760 --> 00:12:51.350 align:middle line:90%
call California.

00:12:51.350 --> 00:12:55.670 align:middle line:84%
But the redwoods and the oaks
and the grasslands are gone.

00:12:55.670 --> 00:12:58.340 align:middle line:84%
The chaparral-covered
hills are gone.

00:12:58.340 --> 00:13:01.880 align:middle line:84%
And in their place is this
well-developed tropical forest

00:13:01.880 --> 00:13:05.390 align:middle line:84%
of really truly
immense proportions.

00:13:05.390 --> 00:13:07.730 align:middle line:84%
I've spent, as an
anthropologist, a lot of time

00:13:07.730 --> 00:13:09.740 align:middle line:84%
in tropical regions
of the world,

00:13:09.740 --> 00:13:12.200 align:middle line:84%
and I've seen
tropical rainforest.

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:16.130 align:middle line:84%
And this looks to me
like tropical forest.

00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:18.710 align:middle line:84%
Now, if this is in
fact California,

00:13:18.710 --> 00:13:22.130 align:middle line:84%
and I believe that
it is, it reveals

00:13:22.130 --> 00:13:25.370 align:middle line:84%
that the worst case scenario
for the greenhouse warming

00:13:25.370 --> 00:13:27.200 align:middle line:90%
has apparently happened.

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:31.040 align:middle line:84%
And there's been a biome shift
in which the tropical regions

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:33.710 align:middle line:84%
of the world have expanded
out of the tropics

00:13:33.710 --> 00:13:36.590 align:middle line:84%
and into the temperate regions,
with the temperate regions

00:13:36.590 --> 00:13:39.980 align:middle line:84%
being displaced
further to the north.

00:13:39.980 --> 00:13:43.250 align:middle line:84%
It seems that there has been
a worldwide climatic shift

00:13:43.250 --> 00:13:48.680 align:middle line:84%
and that he is living
in the greenhouse world.

00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:53.060 align:middle line:84%
Now, up until this moment, I
knew about greenhouse warming,

00:13:53.060 --> 00:13:55.580 align:middle line:84%
but I wasn't particularly
interested in it.

00:13:55.580 --> 00:13:57.650 align:middle line:84%
At this point, I became
very interested in it,

00:13:57.650 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:84%
and I began to read the
scientific literature

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:04.280 align:middle line:84%
about this very important
issue, in my opinion.

00:14:04.280 --> 00:14:07.280 align:middle line:84%
Of course, this was 10
years ago, 15 years ago when

00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:09.140 align:middle line:90%
this actually began for me.

00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:11.180 align:middle line:84%
Today, of course, we're
seeing the results

00:14:11.180 --> 00:14:14.510 align:middle line:84%
of what has been happening
over the last 10 or 15 years.

00:14:14.510 --> 00:14:16.610 align:middle line:84%
And it appears that this
greenhouse phenomenon

00:14:16.610 --> 00:14:18.680 align:middle line:90%
is very much in process.

00:14:18.680 --> 00:14:22.460 align:middle line:84%
And, in my opinion, it's
very disturbing information,

00:14:22.460 --> 00:14:23.360 align:middle line:90%
very critical.

00:14:23.360 --> 00:14:26.040 align:middle line:84%
>> What has happened
to California?

00:14:26.040 --> 00:14:30.320 align:middle line:84%
>> California has been
inundated by a rising sea,

00:14:30.320 --> 00:14:33.020 align:middle line:84%
which has filled the
Central Valley with water.

00:14:33.020 --> 00:14:35.210 align:middle line:84%
So that the Central
Valley of California,

00:14:35.210 --> 00:14:39.800 align:middle line:84%
the San Joaquin Valley
today, is what Ninoa--

00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:40.850 align:middle line:90%
this man's name is Ninoa.

00:14:40.850 --> 00:14:45.050 align:middle line:84%
It's what Ninoa thinks of is
the Inland Sea, surrounded

00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:48.590 align:middle line:84%
by a long archipelago
of islands to the west

00:14:48.590 --> 00:14:52.700 align:middle line:84%
and a mountainous unexplored
region to the east.

00:14:52.700 --> 00:14:55.370 align:middle line:84%
In this very first instance
of connecting with him,

00:14:55.370 --> 00:14:58.640 align:middle line:84%
he was in the process of
leaving his community.

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:02.180 align:middle line:84%
This is a community not unlike
the feudalistic society that

00:15:02.180 --> 00:15:04.280 align:middle line:90%
existed in Hawaii in the past.

00:15:04.280 --> 00:15:06.470 align:middle line:84%
He is the descendant
of Hawaiian voyagers

00:15:06.470 --> 00:15:11.150 align:middle line:84%
who arrived on the coast roughly
130 years before his time.

00:15:11.150 --> 00:15:13.700 align:middle line:84%
And he's leaving on a
voyage of exploration

00:15:13.700 --> 00:15:15.530 align:middle line:84%
into the lost,
well, you could say,

00:15:15.530 --> 00:15:19.700 align:middle line:84%
the interior of the lost
continent of America.

00:15:19.700 --> 00:15:22.910 align:middle line:90%
This is how he thinks about it.

00:15:22.910 --> 00:15:25.320 align:middle line:84%
When this first
episode came to an end,

00:15:25.320 --> 00:15:28.130 align:middle line:84%
I found myself my conscious
awareness returning

00:15:28.130 --> 00:15:30.830 align:middle line:84%
to my own physical aspect,
which was lying in bed

00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:34.340 align:middle line:90%
next to my wife in Hawaii.

00:15:34.340 --> 00:15:38.540 align:middle line:84%
And I literally lay
there in bed in shock

00:15:38.540 --> 00:15:40.790 align:middle line:84%
for the best part of
an hour, wondering

00:15:40.790 --> 00:15:44.600 align:middle line:90%
what had just happened to me.

00:15:44.600 --> 00:15:47.030 align:middle line:84%
My first thought was that
I might be going crazy,

00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:51.070 align:middle line:84%
because in my world of
straight science, you know--

00:15:51.070 --> 00:15:52.820 align:middle line:84%
You know, I'm not one
of those people that

00:15:52.820 --> 00:15:56.000 align:middle line:84%
studied for decades at the
knees of the wisdom masters,

00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:59.510 align:middle line:84%
practicing meditation and
yoga, hoping for visions

00:15:59.510 --> 00:16:01.010 align:middle line:90%
and transcendent experiences.

00:16:01.010 --> 00:16:03.020 align:middle line:84%
I was not looking,
I was not seeking,

00:16:03.020 --> 00:16:04.700 align:middle line:90%
for visionary experience.

00:16:04.700 --> 00:16:07.790 align:middle line:84%
It began for me in a
very spontaneous way.

00:16:07.790 --> 00:16:11.570 align:middle line:84%
But over the next four years
of living on my farm in Hawaii

00:16:11.570 --> 00:16:14.780 align:middle line:84%
these visionary
experiences continued.

00:16:14.780 --> 00:16:17.600 align:middle line:84%
And I found my conscious
awareness continually drawn

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:20.840 align:middle line:84%
into the connection
with this man's mind.

00:16:20.840 --> 00:16:25.250 align:middle line:84%
Then there came an interesting
moment where he had a dream.

00:16:25.250 --> 00:16:29.030 align:middle line:84%
And in his dream, he found
his mind drawn backwards,

00:16:29.030 --> 00:16:30.800 align:middle line:84%
and he found
himself in the mind,

00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:34.150 align:middle line:84%
in the body, of a man
who was living in Hawaii.

00:16:34.150 --> 00:16:35.210 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:16:35.210 --> 00:16:36.740 align:middle line:90%
It was me.

00:16:36.740 --> 00:16:39.765 align:middle line:84%
And after this experience,
his very first hit--

00:16:39.765 --> 00:16:41.390 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting,
just talking about it

00:16:41.390 --> 00:16:45.320 align:middle line:84%
I have chicken skin all over me,
like the Hawaiians would say.

00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:47.180 align:middle line:84%
His very first hit
was that he had

00:16:47.180 --> 00:16:52.130 align:middle line:84%
connected with the spirit
of one of his ancestors.

00:16:52.130 --> 00:16:56.210 align:middle line:84%
Now, as I say that to
you, at that moment,

00:16:56.210 --> 00:16:58.130 align:middle line:84%
this whole dynamic
shifted for me.

00:16:58.130 --> 00:17:00.800 align:middle line:84%
I had never considered the
fact that this man might

00:17:00.800 --> 00:17:03.470 align:middle line:84%
be one of my descendants,
or even that he might

00:17:03.470 --> 00:17:05.589 align:middle line:90%
be one of my descendant selves.

00:17:05.589 --> 00:17:06.530 align:middle line:90%
Uh huh.

00:17:06.530 --> 00:17:10.010 align:middle line:84%
It threw the whole thing into an
entirely new framework for me,

00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:13.220 align:middle line:84%
to regard this man as
a possible descendant.

00:17:13.220 --> 00:17:15.470 align:middle line:84%
And it's quite interesting
because a number of folks

00:17:15.470 --> 00:17:17.480 align:middle line:84%
have pointed out to
me that I didn't start

00:17:17.480 --> 00:17:19.460 align:middle line:84%
having these
visionary experiences

00:17:19.460 --> 00:17:24.329 align:middle line:84%
until my wife Jill was
pregnant with our first child.

00:17:24.329 --> 00:17:25.819 align:middle line:84%
So it's almost as
though there had

00:17:25.819 --> 00:17:29.150 align:middle line:84%
to be some sort of genetic
contribution to the future

00:17:29.150 --> 00:17:33.260 align:middle line:84%
which I had committed myself
to, and then something locked

00:17:33.260 --> 00:17:35.960 align:middle line:90%
into place and it began.

00:17:35.960 --> 00:17:39.050 align:middle line:84%
It's almost as though it
became possible at that moment.

00:17:39.050 --> 00:17:40.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Why you?

00:17:40.850 --> 00:17:42.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Why me?

00:17:42.080 --> 00:17:43.100 align:middle line:90%
Why me, lord?

00:17:43.100 --> 00:17:45.980 align:middle line:84%
You know, I used to wonder
this at the beginning.

00:17:45.980 --> 00:17:46.910 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:17:46.910 --> 00:17:50.030 align:middle line:90%


00:17:50.030 --> 00:17:52.460 align:middle line:84%
"Spiritwalker" is
the study, it's

00:17:52.460 --> 00:17:55.510 align:middle line:84%
really the story, of
my initiation crisis--

00:17:55.510 --> 00:17:57.470 align:middle line:90%
a classic initiation crisis.

00:17:57.470 --> 00:18:00.170 align:middle line:84%
And it was very much like
a crisis in the sense

00:18:00.170 --> 00:18:02.960 align:middle line:90%
that I lost all my bearings.

00:18:02.960 --> 00:18:06.110 align:middle line:84%
I found myself wandering
aimlessly, kind of sleepwalking

00:18:06.110 --> 00:18:10.700 align:middle line:84%
through my life, looking at
things with entirely new eyes,

00:18:10.700 --> 00:18:13.220 align:middle line:90%
seeing with entirely new eyes.

00:18:13.220 --> 00:18:15.470 align:middle line:84%
"Spiritwalker" is my
initiation crisis.

00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:18.650 align:middle line:84%
"Medicinemaker," the second
book, documents my recovery

00:18:18.650 --> 00:18:20.900 align:middle line:90%
when I came back to California.

00:18:20.900 --> 00:18:22.670 align:middle line:90%
Why me?

00:18:22.670 --> 00:18:25.310 align:middle line:84%
I had a chance to cross trails
with a traditional Hawaiian

00:18:25.310 --> 00:18:27.980 align:middle line:90%
kahuna many years later.

00:18:27.980 --> 00:18:30.680 align:middle line:84%
And I posed that
question to her.

00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:33.313 align:middle line:84%
I downloaded some of
this story to her.

00:18:33.313 --> 00:18:35.480 align:middle line:84%
And it was very interesting
because she looked at me

00:18:35.480 --> 00:18:37.730 align:middle line:84%
and she said, you
know, Dr. Hank,

00:18:37.730 --> 00:18:42.080 align:middle line:84%
you may never fully understand
why you had these experiences.

00:18:42.080 --> 00:18:43.700 align:middle line:84%
She said, most
people who vision,

00:18:43.700 --> 00:18:46.310 align:middle line:84%
most people who have the
deep mystic experience,

00:18:46.310 --> 00:18:51.230 align:middle line:84%
for most of them the deep
prayer is a silent one.

00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:52.388 align:middle line:90%
Those were her words.

00:18:52.388 --> 00:18:54.680 align:middle line:84%
And of course, what she was
saying was that most people

00:18:54.680 --> 00:18:59.090 align:middle line:84%
cannot take this raw material
of this particular dimension

00:18:59.090 --> 00:19:03.230 align:middle line:84%
and translate it into a form
which is meaningful for others.

00:19:03.230 --> 00:19:04.693 align:middle line:90%
In my case, she said, now, look.

00:19:04.693 --> 00:19:06.110 align:middle line:84%
She said, you may
never understand

00:19:06.110 --> 00:19:08.600 align:middle line:84%
why you had these experiences,
but it's very tempting

00:19:08.600 --> 00:19:10.190 align:middle line:84%
to say that you had
them for a reason.

00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:12.350 align:middle line:84%
Because look, you've
got a PhD from Berkeley,

00:19:12.350 --> 00:19:14.600 align:middle line:84%
you've got credentials,
you're a mainstream scientist,

00:19:14.600 --> 00:19:16.600 align:middle line:84%
you're a teacher, you're
a writer, you can talk,

00:19:16.600 --> 00:19:17.960 align:middle line:90%
you can communicate.

00:19:17.960 --> 00:19:20.030 align:middle line:84%
She said, I think
you've been given

00:19:20.030 --> 00:19:22.230 align:middle line:90%
this information for a reason.

00:19:22.230 --> 00:19:24.620 align:middle line:84%
Then we had a very long
conversation, some of which

00:19:24.620 --> 00:19:26.930 align:middle line:84%
is documented in
"Medicinemaker,"

00:19:26.930 --> 00:19:31.190 align:middle line:84%
about the nature of people
who can see the future

00:19:31.190 --> 00:19:33.290 align:middle line:84%
and how they very often
come into relationship

00:19:33.290 --> 00:19:34.880 align:middle line:90%
with certain spirits.

00:19:34.880 --> 00:19:36.710 align:middle line:84%
And in Hawaii, of
course, that spirit

00:19:36.710 --> 00:19:39.380 align:middle line:84%
was Pele, the
volcano goddess, who

00:19:39.380 --> 00:19:42.760 align:middle line:84%
often came into contact
with visionaries-- what

00:19:42.760 --> 00:19:46.130 align:middle line:90%
are called "kaula" in Hawaiian.

00:19:46.130 --> 00:19:47.690 align:middle line:84%
She said, it's very
tempting to think

00:19:47.690 --> 00:19:50.450 align:middle line:84%
that you have been given this
information for a reason.

00:19:50.450 --> 00:19:54.770 align:middle line:84%
So she said, your job is
to go back to your computer

00:19:54.770 --> 00:19:56.840 align:middle line:84%
and write this as
it really happened.

00:19:56.840 --> 00:19:59.370 align:middle line:84%
>> I understand you were going
to write this as fiction.

00:19:59.370 --> 00:20:00.875 align:middle line:90%
>> I was.

00:20:00.875 --> 00:20:02.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's fantastic
when you think about it.

00:20:02.750 --> 00:20:04.030 align:middle line:90%
Time traveling.

00:20:04.030 --> 00:20:06.230 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's virtually
100 years ago that H.G.

00:20:06.230 --> 00:20:08.180 align:middle line:90%
Wells wrote "The Time Machine"--

00:20:08.180 --> 00:20:10.190 align:middle line:90%
almost 100 years ago to the day.

00:20:10.190 --> 00:20:11.940 align:middle line:84%
Now, I read that
when I was a boy,

00:20:11.940 --> 00:20:13.700 align:middle line:84%
but I never in a
million years would

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:17.000 align:middle line:84%
have thought that such a
phenomenon like time traveling

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:18.900 align:middle line:90%
might actually be possible.

00:20:18.900 --> 00:20:21.170 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things I've
tried to do in these books

00:20:21.170 --> 00:20:23.840 align:middle line:84%
is come from the position
of both the scientist

00:20:23.840 --> 00:20:24.830 align:middle line:90%
and the mystic.

00:20:24.830 --> 00:20:26.563 align:middle line:84%
>> What do your
colleagues think of this?

00:20:26.563 --> 00:20:28.190 align:middle line:90%
>> My colleagues.

00:20:28.190 --> 00:20:31.670 align:middle line:84%
My colleagues are strangely
silent about all of this,

00:20:31.670 --> 00:20:35.840 align:middle line:84%
possibly because I work
with them and they know me.

00:20:35.840 --> 00:20:40.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm also sitting on a lot of
data, and they want my data.

00:20:40.370 --> 00:20:43.120 align:middle line:84%
It will be easiest for them
not to say anything at all,

00:20:43.120 --> 00:20:44.420 align:middle line:90%
I think.

00:20:44.420 --> 00:20:46.940 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I myself did this
when I was a graduate student

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:47.840 align:middle line:90%
in anthropology.

00:20:47.840 --> 00:20:50.755 align:middle line:84%
And people would ask me
about Castaneda's work.

00:20:50.755 --> 00:20:52.130 align:middle line:84%
I was very much
